sd=Location Data Management	This service domain maintain details of the use and state of locations of interest to the bank. This can include both physical and virtual addresses. It is used to check for valid use and for sales/marketing activities	A new prospect provides an address as their place of residence. It is checked to be a valid/known location for residential use.	The maintenance of location details is used to check the validity, allowed use and occupancy of locations - both physical and virtual. This information can be augmented using external directory services when appropriate. The information is used for authentication and security purposes, and can also be used for interactive location based sales and marketing when combined with location tracking services/capabilities
sdpath=location-data-management
crpath=location-directory-entry
crr=Location Directory Entry Instance
mcr=Location Directory Entry
bqs=Location Use Occupancy
CONFIG
LocationDirectoryEntry	initiate	Register a location in the catalog		initiateLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
LocationDirectoryEntry	update	Update details about the location's directory entry		updateLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
LocationDirectoryEntry	control	Control the handling of a location entry (e.g. terminate)		controlLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
LocationDirectoryEntry	exchange	Accept, verify, reject etc. details of a location directory entry		exchangeLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
LocationDirectoryEntry	request	Request manual intervention with an entry (e.g. refresh content)		requestLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
LocationDirectoryEntry	retrieve	Retrieve details about a location directory entry		retrieveLocationDirectoryEntry		#desc
